So this is how most, if not all of out DaoImpl tests are structured
public class DummyDaoImpl extends BaseFhirDao {

}

public class DummyDaoImplTest extends BaseModuleContextSensitiveTest {

      @Autowired
      @Qualifier("sessionFactory")
      private SessionFactory sessionFactory;

      private DummyDaoImpl dao;

      @Before
      public void setup() {
        dao = new DummyDaoImpl();
        dao.setSessionFactory(sessionFactory);
      }
}
So if you want to use the same structure for testing from another different module with fhir2 as a dependency, it won't work because of @Setter(AccessLevel.PROTECTED).
dao.setSessionFactory(sessionFactory); will not be available.
Alternatively, you can rely on spring context by auto-wiring DummyDaoImpl instead of using its an instance (Not sure if it can work)

